            <div id="idea"class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                  <span class="panel-title lead"><i class="fa fa-newspaper fa-lg"></i> Passages</span>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body lead">
                    <div class="panel-body-text">
                  On Infinity Forum, one posts “passages” which can be text, code, image, video, and more. Passages can also contain more passages (subpassages). Passages can be projects, which allow only certain members to add subpassages, or they can be tasks, which sort their subpassages by rank, or forum posts, whose subpassages are listed in the order they were posted. 
              </div>
                  <!-- <button class="btn">Launch Your Idea</button> -->
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>
            <div id="information"class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                  <span class="panel-title lead"><i class="fa fa-star fa-lg"></i> Stars</span>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body lead">
                    <div class="panel-body-text">
                  All passages on Infinity Forum are ranked by stars. You can give a free star to a passage by pressing the star button, or give additional stars you have earned from your posts. Stars are created when users donate money to the site, granting them an equivalent amount of stars as they donated money. Stars are also created when posts with sources get starred, as every source gets starred when a post gets starred.
              </div>
                  <!-- <button class="btn btn-success">Learn Something New</button> -->
                </div>
            </div>
            <br>
            <div id="collaboration"class="panel panel-default">
